{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 376978, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "81147", "body": "[b]Some Lore about this guy, taken from WoWWiki:[/b]\n[quote]Tirion Fordring was one of the first five Knights of the Silver Hand selected by Archbishop Alonsus Faol, and was one of the heroes of the Second War. He later became Lord of Mardenholde Keep in Hearthglen before being stripped of his title and exiled for defending an orc, Eitrigg. Following the recent death of his son Taelan Fordring, Tirion committed himself to refounding the order of the Silver Hand. He now leads the Argent Crusade, an organization consisting of the old Knights of the Silver Hand and the Argent Dawn, against the Lich King and the Scourge. To this day he remains good friends with the orc veteran Eitrigg. [/quote]\n\n[b]He can also be found in [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=20349]Old Hillsbrad Foothills[/url] (hes younger version of course) and in [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=12126]Western Plagued Lands[/url], being involved in Death Knights chain quest.[/b]", "date": "2008-09-15T11:42:07-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-09-15T11:49:36-05:00", 2, "81147"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 394000, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "adashiel", "body": "The conversation he has with the disguised Darion Mograine ([npc=30377]) at the Argent Vanguard in Icecrown:\n\n[quote][b]Highlord Tirion Fordring says:[/b] The Lich King reacted swiftly to the breach. Faster than I anticipated.\n[b]The Ebon Watcher says:[/b] You are dealing with a being that holds within it the consciousness of the most cunning, intelligent, and ruthless individuals to ever live.\n[b]The Ebon Watcher says:[/b] The Lich King is unlike any foe that you have ever faced, Highlord. Though you bested him upon the holy ground of Light's Hope Chapel, you tread now upon his domain.\n[b]The Ebon Watcher says:[/b] You cannot win. Not like this...\n[b]Highlord Tirion Fordring says:[/b] What would you have me do, Darion?\n[b]The Ebon Watcher says:[/b] Nothing. There is nothing that you can do while the Light binds you. It controls you wholly, shackling you to the ground with its virtues.\n[b]Highlord Tirion Fordring says:[/b] Choose your words wisely, death knight. You stand amidst the company of the devoted.\n[i]The Ebon Watcher shakes his head.[/i]\n[b]The Ebon Watcher says:[/b] Look upon the field, Highlord. The Lich King has halted your advance completely and won the upper hand!\n[b]The Ebon Watcher says:[/b] The breach you created was sealed with Nerubian webbing almost as quickly as it was opened.\n[b]The Ebon Watcher says:[/b] Your soldiers are being used as living shields to stave off artillery fire in the Valley of Echoes, allowing the forces of the Lich King to assault your base without impediment.\n[b]The Ebon Watcher says:[/b] The Lich King knows your boundaries, Highlord. He knows that you will not fire on your own men. Do you not understand? He has no boundaries. No rules to abide. \n[b]Highlord Tirion Fordring says:[/b] We will do this with honor, Darion. We will not sink to the levels of the Scourge to be victorious. To do so would make us no better than the monster that we fight to destroy!\n[b]The Ebon Watcher says:[/b] Then you have lost, Highlord.[/quote]\n\nYou'll only be able to witness this conversation early on in the Argent Crusade quest line.  In later phases, the Ebon Watcher departs.", "date": "2008-10-01T17:38:23-05:00", "rating": 29, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-10-20T08:33:39-05:00", 5, "adashiel"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 403149, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "192801", "body": "He's wielding [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=13262]Ashbringer[/url] so perhaps there is a relation between him and the supposed Ashbringer quest line.", "date": "2008-10-11T18:22:49-05:00", "rating": 11, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "In old hillsbrad at the inn in southshore, the player can witness the \"creation\" of the ashbringer by the older (Alexandros) Mograine, and Fordring is one of those in attendance along with some other familiar names.  Darion Mograine (son of Alexandros and brother to the scarlet commander found in SM) somehow gets his hand on the ashbringer, then gives it to Tirion Fordring at the Battle at Light's Hope Chapel as part of the Death Knight quest line. Then Darion Mograine (the ebon watcher) devotes his death knights to the cause of the Argent dawn to help destroy the lich king.   After that in No", "creationdate": "2008-10-11T18:22:50-05:00", "id": 371873, "rating": 5, "commentid": 403149, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "47990", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Actaully you get it for him in a [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?quest=11289]quest[/url]!", "creationdate": "2008-10-23T18:15:43-05:00", "id": 52316, "rating": 5, "commentid": 403149, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kleb", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-10-19T10:37:31-05:00", 1, "192801"]}
