{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 2368802, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Bagheera", "body": "Can confirm clicking on him (At The Frozen Throne) in the Legion Pre-patch he says the following;\n\n\"There... isn't much time\"\n\"Help me\"\n\"So... weak\"\n\"*Coughing noises*\"\n\n\n\nPerhaps this is homage to Tirion's fate in the Legion.\n\n[b]* Possible Broken Shore Spoilers*[/b]\n\n\n\nI would like to think this is an Easter egg.\n\nMaybe a part of his past self is telling us he is not completely lost just yet. That even though we saw him attacked and finally fall into the fel pools on the Broken sure, that he still survived and is somewhere... hanging on. \n\n... However this could also be referring to the part of the scenario where he is within the clutches of Gul'dan before his \"demise\". Though if this was the case, clicking on Tirion and receiving absolute silence would be more horrifying.\n\nI would love for the first part of the above to be a possibility.  \nMaybe, just maybe Tirion will be the Bolvar of Legion. \n\nNo longer able to wield the Ashbringer (Tainted from the fight) the Ashbringer is passed down to its next hero(es) without him gone.\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=94595/tirion-fordrings-soul]However anything could be a possibility, as other theories suggest.[/url]", "date": "2016-08-16T09:38:17-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "just a bug dude, blizz fucked something up", "creationdate": "2016-10-13T23:35:31-05:00", "id": 996059, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2368802, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Calibrated", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-08-16T12:16:03-05:00", 2, "Bagheera"]}
