{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 256088, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Cross88", "body": "Best quest-giver NPC [i]ever[/i]. If you have enemies chasing you when you run up to him, he'll activate devotion aura, which affects you too, and will heal you with holy light as he fights the enemies.", "date": "2008-03-19T22:22:45-05:00", "rating": 63, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "And that's AWESOME because there are very few that actually react to what's happening to you, the lousy ingrates.  I tried it out just because of that...his devotion aura seemed quite hefty to me at about 1100 armor (about a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=48941]rank 9[/url] version of the spell), but since I've never paid much attention to it while in groups, [i]any[/i] bonus to armor is a plus for a slightly squishy hunter (not that I really needed it).  I'm glad I took some time to do his quests...I really enjoyed the ones he has in Icecrown.  I'm glad he was redeemed after all because h", "creationdate": "2008-03-19T22:22:46-05:00", "id": 443683, "rating": 7, "commentid": 256088, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Eilonthay", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If there were a Tirion Fordring fan club I'd be a charter member.  After reading this I had to try it - as Eilonthay said, not many NPCs will notice you are in trouble. City guards will fight mobs you bring close, but they're obviously defending the city, not you. I've never seen one heal.  Tirion will also cast, as the abilities list suggests, Exorcism and Hammer of Justice. He might not have time to cast all that if it's just one of the plaguebats or plaguehounds that are around there - they die too fast. So if you want to see him use all his abilities, go in the tunnel just north of him and", "creationdate": "2008-03-19T22:22:46-05:00", "id": 453897, "rating": 6, "commentid": 256088, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Auden", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 256447, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "h4xninja", "body": "An awesome Questgiver, 3 simple quests which you can complete simultaneously although the slab of carrian etc quest can take a while because of a low droprate.", "date": "2008-03-20T14:29:03-05:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 336546, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "AusSpyder", "body": "Lord Tirion Fordring was governor of Hearthglen and father of [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=1842]Highlord Taelan Fordring[/url] Who is commander of the Scarlet Crusade.\r\n\r\nHe is the only KNOWN surviving founder of the silver hand ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/?object=25330]Turalyon[/url] not being confirmed as dead would be the second survivor, if he is indeed alive as rumored)\r\n\r\nShortly after the beginning of the WC3 story arch, Tirion, met an old hermit orc named [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=3144]Eitrigg[/url]. Eitrigg was not the mindless savage beast Tirion was used to associating with orcs, and after speaking with him evaluated that Eitrigg was no threat to his people and gave his word that he would be allowed to live out his years in peace and solitude.\r\n\r\nWhen it became knowledge that Tirion had given his word to the orc he was exiled by [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?object=2082]Uther[/url] and stripped of the light. He was then banished and forced to live in exile, Eitrigg was scheduled to be hung.\r\n\r\nUnable to sit by as Eitrigg, Tirion vowed to do whatever he was able to rescue him, eventually succeeding in rescuing him from the gallows.\r\n\r\nThe light returned to Tirion when he pleaded with it to help him save the innocent Eitrigg's life.\r\n\r\nHis entire quest chain, although hard to do now due to it involving the rarely done Strat live instance, is among one of the most enjoyable and lore heavy chains in the entire game.\r\n\r\nHe starts you out with the simple \"Bring a little order to the land\" style quests:\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=5542]Demon Dogs[/url]\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=5543]Blood Tinged Skies[/url]\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=5544]Carrion Grubbage[/url]\r\n\r\nAnd then sets you out on what is IMO the most awesome pre BC quest chain in the game (this coming from someone who has played only horde in his 4 years)\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=5742]Redemption[/url] is the beginning of the 8 part lore heavy quest chain.", "date": "2008-07-26T04:47:35-05:00", "rating": 43, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "well that above is exact Chris Metzen's first novel from the Warcraft saga: Of Blood and Honor. Every Warcraft fan should read it", "creationdate": "2012-01-06T10:17:53-06:00", "id": 505358, "rating": 0, "commentid": 336546, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "geesus", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 365461, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "DrPancake", "body": "Kited Taelen Fordring to him, and They Fought.\n\nTaelen Won. By a lot. Mainly because he's 3 levels above and has 4 adds.\n\nI feel terrible :(\n\nEdit: To make up for my crime, I kited them back to eachother and Healspammed Tirion, and after a very long time he eventually won.", "date": "2008-08-30T14:24:38-05:00", "rating": 71, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "cant do that now since hes a raid boss now lol", "creationdate": "2008-12-05T23:54:55-06:00", "id": 367639, "rating": -1, "commentid": 365461, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "238760", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "but now if Tirion Fordring had the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=13262]Ashbringer[/url], it wouldve been [b]quite[/b] an obvious fight who wouldve won ;)", "creationdate": "2009-06-08T19:57:42-05:00", "id": 102716, "rating": 22, "commentid": 365461, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "346361", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If anyone loses in battle while wielding the Ashbringer, I'm pretty sure there's no hope for them.", "creationdate": "2009-06-20T12:47:43-05:00", "id": 411702, "rating": 2, "commentid": 365461, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "fatdog", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ashbringer is amazing against undead, but against the living it's just a normal sword. Tirion wouldn't have fared any better.", "creationdate": "2013-04-24T13:37:09-05:00", "id": 653477, "rating": -1, "commentid": 365461, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Reignac", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-08-30T14:50:15-05:00", 3, "DrPancake"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 509447, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "181923", "body": "Despite being a key NPC in a couple different places in Wrath of the Lich King content, this \"incarnation\" of Tirion is still present in Eastern Plaguelands and his quests are still obtainable.\r\n\r\nMany players new to the game since the release of TBC do not seem to be aware of his quest chain--he is after all, a bit tucked away in a part of EPL that is out of the way compared to the Light's Hope Chapel quest hub--but it's definitely not one to miss if you enjoy quest chains driven heavily by lore.\r\n\r\nHis quests are also a nice way to add to your total for the Loremaster of the Eastern Kingdoms achievement.", "date": "2008-12-14T11:35:49-06:00", "rating": 18, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "What's funny is that you can do his quests as a Death Knight, which is a complete logical impossibility.  By the time you're free to roam, he's no longer the man he was for this chain.", "creationdate": "2009-02-03T12:40:31-06:00", "id": 77652, "rating": 29, "commentid": 509447, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LostDrewid", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "just look at it this way.  as a DK, you are only remembering about when you did those quests while you were still alive.  remember that from a lore point of view, all DK's were heroes of the aliance/horde, seasoned adventurers, who died in combat against the undead, and were raised again to fight for the lich king.  so, for normal players doing this quests is their first time.  and for DK's is just their way of remembering their actions of the past, to regain their past memories and glory.", "creationdate": "2009-03-18T07:30:43-05:00", "id": 86153, "rating": 41, "commentid": 509447, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 264, "username": "Rankkor", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yeah right, I can personally guarantee a blizzard employee just read that and is bolting to his office shouting 'OH NOES, I SCREWED UP! I BROKE WARCRAFT!'", "creationdate": "2009-03-22T08:25:21-05:00", "id": 395453, "rating": 1, "commentid": 509447, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "339589", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
