{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 860223, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rankkor", "body": "[quote]Dk's are alive, they were enslaved by the lich king...[/quote]\r\n\r\no really? and tell me then, what exactly is instructor razovius doing to the huge pile of corpses on the second floor of acherus? waking them up?\r\n\r\nthat pile is made of corpses of heroes of the alliance and the horde, who died in combat against the scourge.\r\n\r\nthese are resurected, but not with the plage wich turns them into zombies, rather they are resurected with necromancy, and black magic, thus allowing them to remain in a state of relative preservation.\r\n\r\na death knight that falls into pieces is kinda useless, they need these knights to have hard durable bodys, and that's the reason Death knights are a rare breed of undead that still look rather well preserved, but are still undead.\r\n\r\nfor gameplay reasons player-DK's are treated as simple Humanoids, much the same way as forsaken players are treated as such, to make the game balanced, but trust me bro' on lore all DK's are undead. (why do you think they have the creepy voices? for fun?)", "date": "2009-10-06T01:31:49-05:00", "rating": 24, "indent": 0, "roles": 264, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
