{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 1136149, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Varleen", "body": "I see it this way: player-character dks are in a state between live and undeath. They are alive but their bodies show signs of undeads. After all they are resurrected using a form of necromancy. Besides, if you remember, Koltira mentions something about having broken ribs and internal bleed. That means they are somehow alive.", "date": "2010-10-06T13:10:49-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 1179674, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "karlww", "body": "He's gone :( Now in Hearthglen. I miss hermit-tirion.", "date": "2010-11-24T00:02:36-06:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yeah, he's not there anymore, but at least he's back home, which I thought was pretty cool.  He deserved that at the very least.  Hearthglen looks so much better these days and despite the way everyone there treated him when he was banished, I'm sure they're probably pretty happy that [i]the[/i] Highlord of the Argent Crusade is there to keep them safe.  The druids have made a pretty good dent into cleaning up WPL as best as they can as quickly as possible, but with the restoration of EPL still a long way off and right next door, it's just as well that Tirion is in the region to keep an eye on", "creationdate": "2010-11-24T00:02:37-06:00", "id": 494338, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1179674, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Eilonthay", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
