{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 330340, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rarehunter", "body": "Maybe one of the last founders of Knights of the Silver Hand still alive in Azeroth. In Wotlk the Knights of the Silver Hand faction will return.\n\nYou can find the younger, lesser of rank [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=20349]Tirion Fordring[/url] in Caverns of Time: Old Hillsbrad Foothills in a meeting with other members of the Knights of the Silver Hand.\n\nEdited. Thanks, NekoSOM.", "date": "2008-07-19T14:45:56-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I believe what he meant to say was that he was one of the only *founders* of the Silver Hand still alive on Azeroth, as there were only 6 paladins originally (Alonsus Faol, Uther the Lightbringer, Tirion Fordring, Turyalon, Saidan Dathrohan and Gavinrad the Dire).  While Turaylon is most likely still alive, it is highly unlikely that he is anywhere in Azeroth.  All the rest are dead.  Since a \"Knight of the Silver Hand\" is nothing more than a technical term for a Paladin (not counting Blood Knights) there are plenty of Knights of the Silver Hand left, though likely not all that many that were ", "creationdate": "2008-07-19T14:45:57-05:00", "id": 369235, "rating": 3, "commentid": 330340, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "128242", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "the knights of the silver hand are in wotlk. they fused with the argent dawn. they are now the argent crusade. Tirion Fordring is one of the original paladins along with the dead Uther and the other ones Arthas killed to get the urn with his fathers ashes to revive Kelthuzad, and also the missing Turalyon.", "creationdate": "2008-12-05T23:50:02-06:00", "id": 62284, "rating": 2, "commentid": 330340, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "238760", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Actually, Faol wasn't a paladin. He just helped create the paladins.", "creationdate": "2009-03-21T12:27:03-05:00", "id": 86735, "rating": 3, "commentid": 330340, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "266285", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Human and Dwarf paladins are Knights of the Silver Hand. Blood Elf paladins are Blood Knights and Draenei paladins are Vindicators. A rumored title for the future Tauren paladin is Sunwalker. So each faction of paladins have their own name for a member of their order.", "creationdate": "2009-10-20T13:28:14-05:00", "id": 128395, "rating": 4, "commentid": 330340, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mrnnj", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "so...its redundent, he was apart of the silver hand", "creationdate": "2010-02-14T02:06:53-06:00", "id": 149008, "rating": 0, "commentid": 330340, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "487104", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-05-03T00:25:15-05:00", 1, "Rarehunter"]}
