{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 280676, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "116582", "body": "This is also the Tirion Fordring from Chris Metzen's Warcraft novel [b][i]Of Blood and Honor[/i][/b].\r\n\r\n\"The noble Paladin, Tirion Fordring, had always believed the savage Orcs to be vile and corrupt. He had spent his life fighting ceaselessly to protect humanity from their foul treachery. But an unexpected act of honor and compassion sets in motion a chain of events that will challenge Tirion's most fundamental beliefs, and force him to decide once and for all who are the men -- and who are the monsters.\"\r\n\r\n http://www.wowwiki.com/Of_Blood_and_Honor", "date": "2008-05-01T20:44:21-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-05-01T20:47:43-05:00", 4, "116582"]}
